# Weekend Planner Entitlement Update Notes

Date: 2026-06-18

## Scope implemented
- Enforced 3-tier planner entitlement model in server routes and client UI:
  - `weekend_pro`: full planner with season calendar toggle + unlimited calendar feeds.
  - `insider`: full planner actions with active calendar feed cap at 2.
  - `explorer` / unverified: read-only planner mode with gated actions and upgrade CTA.

## Code updates
- `apps/ti-web/app/_components/planner/PlannerClient.tsx`
  - Swapped `isPaid` prop for `plannerEntitlement: TiTier`.
  - Added canonical entitlements: `isExplorer`, `isInsider`, `isWeekendPro`.
  - Updated `canWritePlanner` and action gates for create/edit/delete/refresh/import/duplicate/assign workflows.
  - Updated calendar gate logic to cap Insider at 2 feeds and keep Weekend Pro unlimited.
  - Updated gate messaging for Explorer vs Insider copy paths.
- `apps/ti-web/app/weekend-planner/page.tsx`
  - Passes `plannerEntitlement` from `tierInfo.tier` into `PlannerClient`.
  - Kept `canUseSavedPlanning` as server-side planner feature gate.
- `apps/ti-web/app/_components/planner/ChildTeamManager.tsx`
  - Added `canWriteProfiles` prop.
  - Explorer/unverified get read-only behavior with blocked action text.
- API routes under `apps/ti-web/app/api/planner/*` now enforce entitlement checks server-side:
  - `children` and `children/[id]`
  - `teams` and `teams/[id]`
  - `events` and `events/[id]`
  - `sources` (`[id]`, `[id]/refresh`, `import-ics`)
  - `events/duplicates/dismiss`, `events/merge`
  - Cap checks updated where applicable (team cap at 2 across user’s planner team rows).

## UAT notes to run
- [ ] Open `/weekend-planner` as explorer, insider, weekend_pro test accounts.
- [ ] Explorer path:
  - [ ] Planner renders as read-only and shows explorer-specific CTA copy.
  - [ ] Manual event create/edit/delete are blocked with read-only messaging.
  - [ ] Source import/refresh/disconnect are blocked with read-only entitlement messaging.
  - [ ] Child and team profile actions (`Add`, `Edit`, `Archive`, `Restore`) are disabled.
  - [ ] API routes return explicit entitlement errors (`not_paid` / 403-style responses) for mutation attempts.
- [ ] Insider path:
  - [ ] Manual event create/edit/delete work.
  - [ ] Can add first and second calendar sources successfully.
  - [ ] Third active calendar source is blocked at the two-calendar limit.
  - [ ] Insider receives copy referencing the 2-calendar active limit.
- [ ] Weekend Pro path:
  - [ ] Manual event create/edit/delete work.
  - [ ] Season calendar mode is available.
  - [ ] Calendar source connection is not limited to two.
- [ ] Family/profile behavior:
  - [ ] Child and team profile lists are visible in explorer mode.
  - [ ] Explorer cannot edit/modify/archive/restore in profile manager.
  - [ ] Archived profiles remain visible but read-only.
- [ ] Analytics:
  - [ ] `planner_entitlement` in action tracking payloads resolves to:
    - `explorer`
    - `insider`
    - `weekend_pro`
  - [ ] Verified sessions are not mislabeled as insider.

## Latest implementation pass (2026-06-18)
- Applied remaining Weekend Planner hardening:
  - `apps/ti-web/app/_components/planner/PlannerClient.tsx`
    - Routed all manual event “Add event” entrypoints through `openManualEventFromTop()` so explorer/unverified cannot bypass gating via duplicate CTA.
    - Added `sanitizeIcsNotesForDisplay()` and applied sanitized ICS notes rendering for list cards.
    - Added inline whitespace-normalization helper used by notes rendering/path.
  - `apps/ti-web/app/_components/planner/PlannerCalendar.tsx`
    - Reworked month navigation in `goToAdjacentRange()` to jump to explicit month starts to avoid edge-date drift in Schedule-X.
    - Added ICS note display sanitizer in calendar event detail.
  - `apps/ti-web/lib/planner/ics-import.ts`
    - Added `sanitizeImportedNotes()` export.
    - Applied note sanitization inside `normalizeIcsEvents()` so imported ICS notes strip URLs and UUID-like tokens at ingestion time.
  - `apps/ti-web/lib/planner/ics-import.test.ts`
    - Added unit tests for sanitizer and unstructured ICS description privacy filtering.

### UAT to add for this pass
- [ ] Explorer/unverified cannot open the manual-event form from any add-event entrypoint (`Header`, `Add manual event`, or future direct path).
- [ ] Imported ICS notes no longer show raw URLs or UUID-like tokens in:
  - card list view
  - calendar detail modal
- [ ] Calendar month nav in month mode moves to the correct next/previous month consistently (no skipped/partial month behavior at boundaries).

### Additional UAT retest focus (post-fix follow-up)
- [ ] ICS edit modal privacy is clean:
  - open a TeamSnap event edit modal and verify:
    - no `Link:` label
    - no raw `https://...` URLs
    - no visible UUID-like fragments
- [ ] Calendar month/week navigation now advances:
  - Month view: starting from June 2026, `‹` goes to May 2026 and `›` to July 2026
  - Week view: `‹`/`›` shift full 7-day windows and labels update accordingly
  - no runtime errors on date-navigation clicks

### UAT Re-test Feedback — 2026-06-18 (local `/weekend-planner`)

- **Environment:** `http://localhost:3001` (tab `1758705939`, Weekend Pro session)
- **Outcome summary:** Test A passed, Tests B and C failed before this follow-up fix.

- **Test A — Explorer add-event entrypoints:** PASS
  - Header tab-bar `Add event` and section card `Add event` both blocked with no mutation attempt.
  - Copy verified as exact: `Upgrade to Insider to unlock planner actions.`
  - Note: `explorer_test@example.com` currently shows `Plan: Insider` in `/account` and is likely a fixture configuration issue.

- **Test B — ICS note sanitization in edit modal:** FAIL (pre-fix)
  - Raw `Link:` label and `https://...` URL remained in Edit modal Notes despite list/cards being clean.
  - Root cause: edit form prefill used raw `e.notes`.

- **Test C — Calendar month/week nav:** FAIL (pre-fix)
  - Month mode `‹`/`›` and week mode `›` did not advance date.

### Follow-up code fixes completed
- `apps/ti-web/app/_components/planner/PlannerClient.tsx`
  - Added ICS edit note prefill sanitation so modal uses `sanitizeIcsNotesForDisplay` output for ICS events.
- `apps/ti-web/app/_components/planner/PlannerCalendar.tsx`
  - Added robust Schedule-X date normalization for `controls.getDate()` and ensures `controls.setDate()` always receives a `Temporal.PlainDate`.
- `apps/ti-web/app/api/planner/events/route.ts`
  - Added API response sanitization for ICS-like events so `notes` no longer return raw URLs/UUID-like text.
